    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So I would propose:\n- every good community widget ends up in the community widget list (link to github + demo if available)\n- for instantsearch.js launch, we (algolia) build some widgets in github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js-$widget. Like instantseach.js-googleMap\n- we list this as a community widget: this is not something in the core and so should not be listed in the main documentation but rather have his own small documentation + demo on gh pages in his github\n\nAs a user it's really important to be able to distinguish the core widgets from the community widgets. jQuery ui for instance do not have the documentation/demos for community widgets on the main website. Which is good, for clarity and maintenance.\n",
